            <head type="main-derived">This young man in bed 25</head>
            
            <p>This <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">young man</add> in bed 25, is H.D.B. of company B. 27th Connecticut. 
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">He was born and raised at</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked" seq="2">His folks live at</add> 
                </subst>
                Northford near New Haven. <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion"> Thoug<!-- I [TJ] agree this should end with an "h" but there is no ascender ending the word --> not more than 21 or thereabout</add> He has
                knocked around the world 
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">a little,</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked" seq="2">considerable,</add> 
                </subst>
                on sea and land&#8212; <del rend="overstrike">had</del> has seen
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">a little</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked" seq="2">some</add> 
                </subst>
                some fighting.&#8212; <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">&#8212; <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">.</add></add><del rend="overstrike">is<del rend="overstrike"><add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">altogether</add></del> a young man that any one would like.</del> I
                <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">have</add> asked him
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">once several hours</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion" seq="2">one time<del rend="overstrike">and another</del></add>
                </subst>
                what I could do for him&#8212;if he did not want a little money, &#38;c.<del rend="overstrike">?</del> No, <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">he answered,</add> he <del rend="overstrike"> had a </del>had all he 
                needed <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">&#8212;had money.</add> &#8212;Once, when he got very low, he
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">thought</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked" seq="2">said</add> 
                </subst>
                that if I could get him a small home-made rice-pudding, he thought he could eat it.  A noble, gentle Washington lady (Mrs. O'C.) hearing this, made the <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">rice</add>
                pudding, and I took it up to him.  He told me afterward he lived upon it for three or four days. <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">He is a
                        <subst>
                        <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">true</del>
                        <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion" seq="2">good example of the</add> 
                        </subst>
                    American young man.  I gave him a pipe as a keepsake.</add> One gets a personal attachment to <del><gap reason="illegible"/></del> <del rend="overstrike"></del>
                <subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike" seq="1">some of these</del>
                    <add place="supralinear" rend="unmarked" seq="2">such</add> 
                </subst>
                young fellows.
            </p>
            
            <p>Then to attend to some of my<add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">little</add> commissions, first referring to my my memoranda.  Bed
                </p>
